Hydraulic System Reservoir - Fluid Level Check and Replenishment

ATA Chapter (Illustrative): 29 — Hydraulic Power
S1000D DMC (Illustrative & Generic): XXXXXX-A-29-13-01-00A-615A-A
Aircraft/Company: Not Specified / Generic Manufacturer


This task involves:

    - Locating and gaining access to the specified hydraulic system reservoir servicing panel/point.
    - Performing necessary safety precautions for working with hydraulic systems and fluids.
    - Visually inspecting the reservoir fluid level indicator (e.g., sight glass, float indicator, or electronic display).
    - Interpreting fluid level markings correctly (e.g., considering system temperature, pressurized/depressurized state).
    - If the fluid level is low, connecting approved hydraulic servicing equipment (ground cart).
    - Replenishing the reservoir with the specified type of hydraulic fluid to the correct level.
    - Disconnecting servicing equipment and ensuring no leaks at connection points.
    - Performing a final visual check for leaks around the reservoir and serviced area.
    - Recording the servicing action.


