Landing Gear Torque Link - Lubrication

ATA Chapter (Illustrative): 32 — Landing Gear
S1000D DMC (Illustrative and Generic): XXXXXX-A-32-11-03-00A-631A-A
Aircraft/Company: Not Specified / Generic Manufacturer


This task involves:

    - Safely gaining access to the specified landing gear torque link assembly (e.g., Main Landing Gear Left Side Torque Link).
    - Cleaning existing grease and contaminants from lubrication points (e.g., grease fittings/zerks, pivot bushings).
    - Applying the specified type and grade of grease using appropriate lubrication equipment (e.g., grease gun with correct nozzle).
    - Ensuring grease is applied until fresh grease is seen extruding from bleed points or as specified, indicating complete lubrication of the joint.
    - Wiping off excess grease.
    - Performing a visual check to confirm proper lubrication and cleanliness.
    - Recording the lubrication task.


